                <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother Cartwright" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother Cartwright</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">Blackwall & Calcutta • c. 1790–1860</p>
              <p class="text-sm mb-3 text-[color:var(--accent)]">⛳ Calcutta Golfing Society</p>
              <blockquote class="text-sm italic my-4 px-3 border-l-2 border-[color:var(--accent)]">
                "Wherever a ship can carry a ball and a bottle, the 19th hole will follow."
              </blockquote>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text)] mb-4">
                Born among the masts of the East India Docks and later a clerk on the route to India, Brother Cartwright turned dockside inns and Calcutta verandas into true 19th holes, stitching the Order’s river‑born traditions into the growing game across the empire.
              </p>
              <a href="/blog" class="text-[color:var(--accent)] hover:underline text-sm">
                Read Their Legend →
              </a>
            </div>

            <!-- Member 7 -->
            <div class="bg-[color:var(--color-card)] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] rounded-lg p-6 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all">
              <div class="w-32 h-32 mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full overflow-hidden">
                <img src="/images/man1950.png" alt="Brother O'Donnell" class="w-full h-full object-cover" />
              </div>
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Brother O'Donnell</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-text-secondary)] mb-3">New York & Long Island, USA • 1895–1970</p>
